# cogno-chain — environment surface (safe defaults; no secrets in this file).
#
# The all-Rust backend is one node + a run-anywhere CLI + a static frontend, so there are very few env
# vars. There are NO follower / relayer / indexer / committee services and NO signing seeds in env: the
# CLI takes keys BY FILE, and every privileged call goes through the committee (there is no sudo).
#
# Canonical per-component examples:
#   • node     — deploy/systemd/cogno.env.example  (DBSYNC_URL + optional RUST_LOG)
#   • frontend — the NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars below, inlined at build (see app/README.md)

# ── node (cogno-chain-node) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Read-only Cardano db-sync the in-protocol observer reads. Absent/unset ⇒ the observer abstains and the
# chain still produces + finalizes. MAINNET PREREQUISITE: FULL (non-pruned), tx_in-enabled (NOT
# --consumed-tx-out), over TLS. The node reads ONLY this (+ optional RUST_LOG) from its environment.
DBSYNC_URL=postgres://cogno_reader:PASSWORD@127.0.0.1:5432/cexplorer
# RUST_LOG=info

# ── frontend (app/, inlined at build — see app/README.md) ──────────────────────────────────
NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=ws://127.0.0.1:9944                 # the node JSON-RPC the SPA reads
NEXT_PUBLIC_BLOCKFROST_PROJECT_ID=                     # preprod project id for the in-browser L1 vault

# ── CIP-8 CI oracle (ci/cip8-oracle/, optional local run) ──────────────────────────────────
# The agreement test shells out to a headless MeshJS fixture in app/ — use the nvm node, not snap.
# NODE_BIN=/home/you/.nvm/versions/node/v22.12.0/bin/node
# APP_DIR=./app
